		<body>
				<p rend="align(center)"><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee> <placeName>Pha.</placeName></p>
				<p>Dear Sir&#33;  Twelve months have now expired since I<lb/> first made your <sic>Aquaintance</sic>&#44; by which you proposed<lb/> sending me one Copy of your Occident.  I have now<lb/> rec&#39;d twelve &#40;without subscribing to them&#41; I am not situa<lb/>ted to procure any subscribers and for my own part <sic>dont</sic><lb/> think it necessary to have it therefore you will please<lb/> discontinue to send it.  I will however pay you for the<lb/> past year &#36;3.00 if you can advise me how to remit the<lb/> money to you it being against the Laws of <placeName>Pa</placeName> to pass<lb/> any Notes under &#36;5 I am at a Loss how to send money<lb/> to you&#44; Silver or Gold is <sic>unconveniend</sic>.  You will<lb/> please advise me as I however pass through your City<lb/> every Spring &#38; Fall I shall be able in <date>September</date> if<lb/> nothing happened to pay you personally or I expect that<lb/> <persName>Mr. Jacob Landsdorfer</persName> or <persName>Mrs Gans Leberman &#38; Co.</persName><lb/> would pay you said <sic>Amount</sic> I can give you an order on<lb/> either of those gentlemen.  I shall be pleased to<lb/> hear from you at an early convenient time<lb/> x sign myself wishing you all future Prosperity</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">very respectfully your obt. <persName role="author">Levi Stern</persName>.</p>
		</body>
